				<li id="16636858" class="cmnt-root" data="21" data-d="1650429876000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578928/Gargoyle's-Black-Halberd" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">20 Apr 2022 00:44</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16636858" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Inferior to the regular Gargoyle Halberd in many ways. Spinning Slash as an AoW is OK in pvp and pve, but the real letdown is not being able to infuse. The default scaling is pretty bad with C/D/D, implying a quality/faith spread, which is waste of stat points if you&apos;re trying to hit damage softcaps as efficiently as possible. <br/><br/>Regular Gargoyle Halberd notably gets the rare S scaling when Heavy Infused, which in of itself already makes it superior to the Black Halberd version. Heavy Infusions also reach their damage softcaps much easier and sooner due to the nature of strength and two-handing. Furthermore you get the added benefit of being able to slap on much better AoWs like Phantom Slash, Sword Dance, Royal Knights Resolve, etc. <br/><br/>For even more salt on the wound, it also has split damage, and one of the split damage types is holy, which a vast majority of late game enemies and bosses have very high resistance to. <br/><br/>This feels like one of those weapons that suffered due to time constraints when they were trying to release the full game. It feels odd that the Black Gargoyle Greatsword is the only Black Gargoyle themed weapon with the unique Black Blade HP DoT effect on its Skill, but the rest of the Black Gargoyle weapons get boring standard AoWs as a holdover. <br/><br/>My educated guess is that all the Black Gargoyle weapons were supposed to have unique red-tinged modified AoWs, to mirror the skills the gargoyle bosses themselves use. But they ran out of time/money and we got standard AoWs instead. <br/><br/>For now, this weapon is not worth your time, especially when there are far superior choices within the Halberd weapon class. I hope this weapon gets at least a buff in scaling, maybe bump that Str scaling up to an A or B. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16636858" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16636858" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>22</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>1</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16636858"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16636858" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16636858"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
