				<li id="16501927" class="cmnt-root" data="15" data-d="1647173839000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578928/Gargoyle's-Black-Halberd" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">13 Mar 2022 08:17</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16501927" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Pro Tips for everyone trying to beat the boss legitimately (no disrespect to those who aren&apos;t).<br/><br/>Strike and roll over and over. You&apos;ll basically want to stay right at his feet. Take the time to learn the timing of his attacks. Roll towards him in most scenarios after his current attack chain then strike and roll out. Depending on your weapon in most cases you can get one or two hits in safely. Slow and steady wins the race on this one don&apos;t get greedy with attacks.<br/><br/>Halberd weapon is easier to dodge then sword imo. Sword has an annoying thrust and a flurry of attacks that&apos;s harder to dodge. <br/><br/>Avoid red tornado looking ability and the red fissure slam. Red tornado is a 3 chain. First two are around the boss the 3rd is at your feet within range. Red fissure is an easy dodge just watch the timing and roll left or right. There are really the only two abilities I found I couldn&apos;t consistently roll towards the boss under his feet.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16501927" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply